GOSPEL OF PHILIP 
– 
FULL REVERSE COHERENT SCAN
YHWH (YHYYH) Codex w/ Numerical Letter Differentiation
Numerical Note: YHWH (יהוה) = 26 base. YHYYH variant = 36 intensified (doubled Yod for covenant/redemptive emphasis). Literal root fidelity to Nag Hammadi Coptic/Greek fragments with YHWH framework alignment.

The one who has the perfect light will not be seen by the rulers nor recognized by them. The rulers will not be able to hold him. This is the perfect man. This is the one who has put on the perfect light. This is the one who has become the light. The light and the darkness, the life and the death, the right and the left are brothers of one another. They cannot be separated. Therefore the good are not entirely good nor the evil entirely evil. This is the way of the world.
The bridal chamber is hidden. It is the holy of holies. It is the place where the light and the darkness mingle. It is the place where the man and the woman become one. It is the place where the image is restored. The one who enters the bridal chamber will not come out again. He will remain in the light forever. This is the true resurrection. This is the true redemption.
The eucharist is the flesh of YHWH. The cup is His blood. The one who receives them in truth becomes perfect. The one who receives them becomes what he eats. He becomes the perfect man. The chrism is the ointment of life. It is the fire that consumes the darkness. Baptism is the water that drowns the old man and raises the new.
The world came into being through a mistake. The one who created it wanted to make it imperishable and immortal. But he failed. He made it mortal. He made it subject to death. But the Father of Truth sent His Son to repair the mistake. The Son came to redeem those who belong to Him. The Son came to reveal the hidden light that is within.
Mary Magdalene was the companion of the Lord. The Lord loved her more than all the disciples. He kissed her often on the mouth. The other disciples were offended. They said: “Why do you love her more than us?” The Lord answered: “Why do I not love you as I love her?”
The names are deceptive. The name of God is not God. The name of the Son is not the Son. The name of the Spirit is not the Spirit. What is generated from the truth is true. What is generated from the name is a name. The truth is not learned by names. The truth is known by the light that is within.
The light is sown in the darkness. The darkness cannot overcome it. The light returns to its root. Those who have the light within them will return to the light. Those who do not have the light will remain in the darkness. This is the mystery of the kingdom of YHWH.
The Gospel of Philip is the revelation of the hidden mysteries. It is the revelation of the sacraments. It is the revelation of the bridal chamber. It is the revelation of the perfect light. It is joy to those who receive it in truth.
